            "name": "Operating Systems",
            "title": "<a href=\"https://mcgill.ca/study/2019-2020/courses/ecse-427\" target=\"_blank\">ECSE 427</a> Operating Systems (3 credits)",
            "overview": "Electrical Engineering : Operating system services, file system organization, disk and cpu scheduling, virtual memory management, concurrent processing and distributed systems, protection and security. Aspects of the DOS and UNIX operating systems and the C programming language. Programs that communicate between workstations across a network.",
