            "name": "EM Transmission and Radiation",
            "title": "<a href=\"https://mcgill.ca/study/2019-2020/courses/ecse-451\" target=\"_blank\">ECSE 451</a> EM Transmission and Radiation (3 credits)",
            "overview": "Electrical Engineering : Microwave transmission through waveguides: impedance matching, microwave devices, filters and resonators; microwave transmission though free space; near and far field behaviour of electromagnetic radiators, simple antennas, antenna arrays, practical antenna parameters; the physics of the radio communication channel: reflection, diffraction and scattering and their macroscopic impact (multipath, fading).",
